[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_a4a53")
title = "Ruboleum Distillation Instructions"
text = "Trial #13: First Successful Cure

Distill Ruboleum by pouring a vial into an opaque flask. Heat the flask with an open flame and wait for the substance to vaporize. When the vapor returns to a purified liquid form and drains into the cup, it should be potent enough to temporarily cure the effects of Vitriscet.

The substance is fast acting, though the amount of time it remains effective is rather insubstantial, only a few minutes. Regardless, this is a breakthrough.

The length it remains effective increases with the number of doses taken, but only to an extent. Any doses taken after the third consecutive dose appear to have no benefit. As such, someone experiencing symptoms can take up to three doses at a time for maximum effectiveness.

Rather concerning, however, is whatever residue should be left inside the distilling flask after the process is finished is nonexistent, which did not happen in the trials with the clear flask."
important = true
metadata/_custom_type_script = "uid://c47e3n15issfv"
